snippet.textDisplay:
150 years ago a young chap from a tiny village from Kushtia,Bangladesh never knew that his music would be played on android devices,
played by foreign musicians with electronic instruments,
listened over radio -satelite relayed world wide web by millions
of people back and forth atlantic and pacific.
Music is universal. Music is
humane. Music transcends border, race and time.

snippet.textDisplay:
This song was written in Bengali, and the entire depth and vibe of this song's lyrics can be expressed only in the Bengali language. No offense, but those inclusions of the Hindi parts totally ruined the vibe. I myself listen to and love a lot of Hindi songs but this song's vibe entirely belongs to the Bengali words only.
Lots of love for the effort though.
